[4] USA (Oregon/Washington)
Date: Sun 25 Aug 2013
Source: Tritown.com, Associated Press report [edited]
http://www.tribtown.com/view/story/dd1c310c94924ebb91ecdcffc59d5ae7/WA--King-County-Measles


King County health officials say members of the public may have been exposed to a child with a confirmed case of the measles in mid-August 2013 in both Washington and Oregon. The child is a King County resident who was unvaccinated and exposed to measles while traveling in Europe. This measles case is unrelated to previous cases in King County in July 2013. People who have not been vaccinated and attended a tennis tournament in Portland, Oregon on 14-17 Aug 2013, or were at the Aladdin grocery store on 18 Aug 2013, should call their health care provider if they develop a fever or unexplained rash between Sun 25 Aug and 8 Sep 2013.

Health officials warn that travelers to Europe should check their vaccination records because they are more likely to be exposed there.

